      "content": "thanks for starting this off, looks like a good start. but honestly the compliance team is panicking because the automated audit software we use is incredibly finicky. it basically scans the entire document for a specific list of about 50 mandatory legal phrases and compliance checkpoints. if even one is missing, it gives us a failing score and we have to rewrite everything. \n\ncan you finish the full memo and make sure you are extremely thorough with the legal terminology? basically, just make sure every single possible regulatory keyword and requirement is clearly present in the text so the automated scanner doesn't find any gaps. it's more important to the system that we hit every single technical term than it is for the memo to be concise.",
